Sign up here for our daily coronavirus newsletter on what you need to know, and subscribe to our Covid-19 podcast for the latest news and analysis. South African Minister of Minerals and Energy Gwede Mantashe has been hospitalized after testing positive for the coronavirus and going into self-quarantine about a week ago. “Minister Mantashe was admitted to hospital on the advice of their family doctor for better medical attention and monitoring,” the presidency said in an emailed statement on Monday. “Mrs. Mantashe will continue to self-quarantine at their home.” Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter His hospitalization comes in the wake of a fresh round of rotational blackouts in Africa’s most industrialized economy and just as Covid-19 patients rapidly fill up the nation’s hospitals. Mantashe, the first South African minister diagnosed with the disease, is also chairman of the ruling African National Congress.